# tkv2 - textFieldR: reactive input label (P2 SPA i18n parity)

Slice `tkv2-textfield-reactive-label` of `specs/ssc-toolkit-v2.md` §5 P2
"SPA i18n parity check": `textFieldR` mirrors `signalLabelButton` — the
label tracks a `Signal[String]` (e.g. a locale switch) instead of being
baked as a static `String` at build time. DOM serialization of the reactive
placeholder/`<label>` text is covered by the emitted SPA/jsdom gate for this
slice; this conformance file keeps the public API, the underlying label
signal, and the `lower()` path live on both lanes.

[signal](std/ui/primitives.ssc)
[textFieldR](std/ui/input.ssc)
[lower](std/ui/lower.ssc)
[defaultTheme](std/ui/theme.ssc)

```scalascript
val value = signal("tfrValue", "")
val label = signal("tfrLabel", "Name")

// The same label signal a locale-switcher would flip — no rebuild of the
// field/value binding needed, unlike a static FieldSpec.label.
println(label())
label.set("Имя")
println(label())

val node = textFieldR(value, label, disabled = false, required = true)
val view = lower(node, defaultTheme)
println("textfieldr-built")
```
